Package: genoformerR
Type: Package
Title: Ancestry-Aware Polygenic Risk Scoring via Transformer (GenoFormer)
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R: person("Shu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "user@example.com")
Description: R wrapper for GenoFormer — a transformer-based ancestry-aware
    polygenic risk scoring pipeline using 1000 Genomes Phase 3 as ancestry
    reference. v0.3.1 adds reference-based projection to gf_ancestry()
    (fit PCA on 1KGP3, project external cohorts in) and gf_windowed_pca()
    (three modes: reference-fit/project-study, study-only, project-into-saved),
    plus gf_save_window_pcas() / gf_load_window_pcas() for consistent scoring
    of new individuals. gf_run_pipeline() gains is_1kg_cohort= to select the
    correct mode automatically and blocks the invalid FLARE+1KGP3 combination.
    All local ancestry methods produce a (N x M x K) per-SNP posterior array
    for dual-level transformer conditioning. Python backend via reticulate.
